<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> hard labor • hard work</xh5><p> <i>hard labor—</i>imprisonment with hard physical work as a punishment: Glynn was sentenced to three months <u>hard labor</u>, but won an appeal.</p><p> <i>hard work—</i>1. difficult and tiring work: It has been <u>hard work</u> to establish order here. 2. <i>(coll.)</i> said of smb. who is difficult to deal with: I had to sit next to Frank at dinner. I don’t know about you, but I find him such <u>hard work</u>.</p> </entry>
